1
00:00:00,001 --> 00:00:03,402
<i> Previously on</i> Lucifer...
I wasn't lying.

2
00:00:03,404 --> 00:00:05,237
I do intend to use
the Flaming Sword

3
00:00:05,239 --> 00:00:06,905
to cut through
the Gates of Heaven.

4
00:00:06,907 --> 00:00:08,307
But what you left out?

5
00:00:08,309 --> 00:00:10,009
I plan on kicking Mum
into Heaven

6
00:00:10,011 --> 00:00:12,211
<i> and slamming the gates</i>
<i> on her backside.</i>

7
00:00:12,213 --> 00:00:14,580
Maybe there's
another piece missing.
MOM:<i> If you find the killer,</i>

8
00:00:14,582 --> 00:00:16,915
<i> then you'll find our piece </i>
<i> of the Flaming Sword.</i>

9
00:00:16,917 --> 00:00:18,283
I went through a
lot this last year,

10
00:00:18,285 --> 00:00:20,586
and improv sort of helped
me reorient myself.

11
00:00:20,588 --> 00:00:21,987
LUCIFER: Amenadiel
told you about our trip

12
00:00:21,989 --> 00:00:23,022
back to Heaven,
didn't he?

13
00:00:23,024 --> 00:00:25,557
(shouts)
<i> You</i> should have told me.

14
00:00:25,559 --> 00:00:28,694
As promised.
This opens a
safety deposit box.

15
00:00:28,696 --> 00:00:31,563
LAPD. Bianca Ruiz,
you're under arrest.

16
00:00:31,565 --> 00:00:35,200
Are you certain this is all that
was in the safety deposit box?

17
00:00:35,202 --> 00:00:36,802
We'll fix it.
There's plenty of time.

18
00:00:36,804 --> 00:00:38,837
MOM:
<i> Just not for me.</i>

19
00:00:38,839 --> 00:00:41,340
God shattered the Flaming Sword
into three distinct pieces.

20
00:00:41,342 --> 00:00:43,342
The Blade of Death,
the Medallion of Life

21
00:00:43,344 --> 00:00:45,544
and the Key that binds
them all together.

22
00:00:45,546 --> 00:00:47,679
Look down.

23
00:00:47,681 --> 00:00:49,982
He entrusted
it to you.

24
00:00:49,984 --> 00:00:51,583
Congrats on nabbing
Queen Tequila.

25
00:00:51,585 --> 00:00:52,985
Well, Chet's still out there,

26
00:00:52,987 --> 00:00:54,319
<i> so this isn't over.</i>

27
00:00:54,321 --> 00:00:55,988
I need what
Zeke really smuggled.

28
00:00:55,990 --> 00:00:57,823
(grunts)

29
00:00:57,825 --> 00:00:59,324
My life is ruined!

30
00:01:04,665 --> 00:01:06,265
(panting)

31
00:01:09,036 --> 00:01:10,035
(metal clicks)

32
00:01:10,037 --> 00:01:13,172
(Mom groans)

33
00:01:13,174 --> 00:01:14,173
(metal clicks)

34
00:01:14,175 --> 00:01:15,941
(Mom groans)

35
00:01:15,943 --> 00:01:17,576
(metal clicking)

36
00:01:17,578 --> 00:01:21,647
♪ Lonely shadows
following me... ♪

37
00:01:21,649 --> 00:01:22,581
Ow.

38
00:01:22,583 --> 00:01:25,951
♪ Lonely ghosts come a-callin' ♪

39
00:01:25,953 --> 00:01:30,589
♪ Lonely voices talking to me ♪

40
00:01:30,591 --> 00:01:34,026
♪ Now I'm gone, now I'm gone,
now I'm gone ♪

41
00:01:34,028 --> 00:01:37,396
♪ And my mother told me ♪

42
00:01:37,398 --> 00:01:39,698
♪ Son, let it be ♪

43
00:01:39,700 --> 00:01:42,801
♪ Sold my soul
to the calling... ♪

44
00:01:42,803 --> 00:01:44,269
(sighs)

45
00:01:44,271 --> 00:01:46,605
♪ Sold my soul to... ♪

46
00:01:46,607 --> 00:01:48,307
Hello?

47
00:01:48,309 --> 00:01:50,642
It's Charlotte Richards.

48
00:01:50,644 --> 00:01:52,744
I need a favor.

49
00:01:52,746 --> 00:01:54,980
♪ Oh, gimme that fire ♪

50
00:01:54,982 --> 00:01:56,348
♪<i> Ooh, ooh, ooh</i> ♪

51
00:01:56,350 --> 00:01:59,118
♪ Oh, gimme that fire ♪

52
00:01:59,120 --> 00:02:00,752
♪<i> Ooh, ooh, ooh</i> ♪

53
00:02:00,754 --> 00:02:03,155
♪ Oh, gimme that. ♪

54
00:02:03,157 --> 00:02:05,023
Would you look at that, Luci?

55
00:02:05,025 --> 00:02:07,860
It really is
the final piece.

56
00:02:07,862 --> 00:02:09,128
Unbelievable.

57
00:02:09,130 --> 00:02:10,996
Oh, no, I believe it.
(pours drink)

58
00:02:10,998 --> 00:02:12,731
It's classic Dad.

59
00:02:12,733 --> 00:02:14,600
Hanging the final piece
of the Flaming Sword

60
00:02:14,602 --> 00:02:17,069
right under our noses--
well...

61
00:02:17,071 --> 00:02:18,137
your nose,

62
00:02:18,139 --> 00:02:19,771
(laughs):
this entire time.

63
00:02:19,773 --> 00:02:21,773
(both laugh)

64
00:02:21,775 --> 00:02:23,041
I know, right?

65
00:02:23,043 --> 00:02:24,376
(laughs)
It's ridiculous.

66
00:02:24,378 --> 00:02:26,378
I mean, if that isn't
the biggest celestial bird

67
00:02:26,380 --> 00:02:27,579
Dad's ever flipped.

68
00:02:27,581 --> 00:02:29,915
What are you talking about?

69
00:02:31,252 --> 00:02:33,585
This means that
I'm the favorite son.

70
00:02:33,587 --> 00:02:37,556
Uh, no, it means that once again

71
00:02:37,558 --> 00:02:41,093
Dad is manipulating us
six ways to Sunday.

72
00:02:41,095 --> 00:02:42,995
But, hey, what's new?

73
00:02:42,997 --> 00:02:44,763
At least we have it now.

74
00:02:44,765 --> 00:02:46,331
So...

75
00:02:50,604 --> 00:02:52,571
Well, hand it over, Brother.

76
00:02:52,573 --> 00:02:54,740
The sword's not
gonna ignite itself.

77
00:02:56,110 --> 00:02:58,710
It... oh, just
give it to me.

78
00:02:58,712 --> 00:03:00,779
Give it to me. Right,
don't be silly, Brother.

79
00:03:00,781 --> 00:03:02,915
You know I'm ten times
stronger than you.

80
00:03:02,917 --> 00:03:04,416
But I'm the favorite.

81
00:03:04,418 --> 00:03:06,084
Oh, right. Of course.

82
00:03:06,086 --> 00:03:07,586
(laughs) That one.

83
00:03:09,190 --> 00:03:11,723
Right, don't
make me hurt you.

84
00:03:11,725 --> 00:03:13,926
Remember, you're not
the angel you once were.

85
00:03:15,763 --> 00:03:18,664
No, Luci, you're
right, I'm not.

86
00:03:18,666 --> 00:03:20,432
Well, oh.

87
00:03:20,434 --> 00:03:22,267
I didn't mean to make you
all broody again.

88
00:03:22,269 --> 00:03:23,502
No, it's okay.

89
00:03:23,504 --> 00:03:26,638
I just need a little time to
process what it all means.

90
00:03:26,640 --> 00:03:28,006
Process?

91
00:03:28,008 --> 00:03:30,542
Okay. Fine.

92
00:03:30,544 --> 00:03:32,344
Suppose we're
in no real rush.

93
00:03:32,346 --> 00:03:34,346
Process away.

94
00:03:34,348 --> 00:03:36,315
I think I've got<i> E.T.</i> on the DVR

95
00:03:36,317 --> 00:03:37,849
if you need a good weep

96
00:03:37,851 --> 00:03:40,919
and a pint of Häagen-Daz
in the freezer if that helps.

97
00:03:40,921 --> 00:03:42,654
♪ ♪

98
00:03:55,636 --> 00:03:56,768
(gasps)

99
00:03:57,972 --> 00:04:00,839
You scared me. God!

100
00:04:00,841 --> 00:04:03,976
Goddess.

101
00:04:03,978 --> 00:04:05,310
But whatever.

102
00:04:05,312 --> 00:04:06,745
I need medical attention.

103
00:04:06,747 --> 00:04:08,247
I'm wounded.

104
00:04:08,249 --> 00:04:10,249
Then go to a hospital.

105
00:04:10,251 --> 00:04:14,319
This isn't exactly
a human injury,

106
00:04:14,321 --> 00:04:16,054
and since you know who,

107
00:04:16,056 --> 00:04:18,056
or rather what I am,

108
00:04:18,058 --> 00:04:21,860
I would appreciate it
if you would just patch me up.

109
00:04:21,862 --> 00:04:23,895
Why does everybody
keep doing this to me?

110
00:04:23,897 --> 00:04:25,697
I am a doctor,

111
00:04:25,699 --> 00:04:28,533
but patching people up
isn't my thing.

112
00:04:28,535 --> 00:04:29,868
Oh.

113
00:04:31,138 --> 00:04:34,139
It is now.

114
00:04:34,141 --> 00:04:37,209
Suppose I could
take a gander.

115
00:04:37,211 --> 00:04:39,544
Wonderful.

116
00:04:42,349 --> 00:04:45,284
I should warn you,
you might have to...

117
00:04:45,286 --> 00:04:47,019
(gasps)

118
00:04:49,056 --> 00:04:50,922
...duck.
What?!

119
00:04:50,924 --> 00:04:52,424
Who did that to you?

120
00:04:52,426 --> 00:04:54,893
I mean, was it Lucifer?

121
00:04:54,895 --> 00:04:56,228
I-I mean...

122
00:04:56,230 --> 00:04:59,031
(laughs nervously)

123
00:04:59,033 --> 00:05:00,432
...not on purpose, you know.

124
00:05:00,434 --> 00:05:02,167
Accidentally,
like with that

125
00:05:02,169 --> 00:05:04,202
Flaming Sword thingy.

126
00:05:04,204 --> 00:05:05,504
(chuckles)

127
00:05:05,506 --> 00:05:07,472
All right, let me see
what I got here.

128
00:05:13,781 --> 00:05:15,547
Okay, duct tape.

129
00:05:17,084 --> 00:05:18,083
Trust me.

130
00:05:18,085 --> 00:05:20,986
This stuff's amazing.

131
00:05:20,988 --> 00:05:25,457
♪ Slow burn ♪

132
00:05:25,459 --> 00:05:26,958
♪ Push it out right. ♪

133
00:05:26,960 --> 00:05:28,593
This is ridiculous.

134
00:05:28,595 --> 00:05:29,761
You have experience

135
00:05:29,763 --> 00:05:31,563
with emotionally fragile men,
don't you?

136
00:05:31,565 --> 00:05:33,131
You're self-aware today.

137
00:05:33,133 --> 00:05:34,366
No, I meant Dan.

138
00:05:34,368 --> 00:05:35,567
Anyway, tell me,

139
00:05:35,569 --> 00:05:38,136
how do you stop them
from overthinking everything?

140
00:05:38,138 --> 00:05:39,738
Who's overthinking?

141
00:05:39,740 --> 00:05:40,672
Amenadiel.

142
00:05:40,674 --> 00:05:42,474
Leave it to him
to turn a compliment

143
00:05:42,476 --> 00:05:44,142
into something
to angst over.

144
00:05:44,144 --> 00:05:46,745
I mean, he should be happy
he's Dad's favorite.

145
00:05:46,747 --> 00:05:49,648
Wait, your dad didn't actually
tell you guys that, did he?

146
00:05:49,650 --> 00:05:53,618
Well, in so many
Sumerian words, yes.

147
00:05:53,620 --> 00:05:57,055
You know, the more
I hear about your dad,

148
00:05:57,057 --> 00:05:59,291
the more I understand
why you're...

149
00:05:59,293 --> 00:06:01,493
you know, you.

150
00:06:01,495 --> 00:06:03,228
ELLA:
Body dump.

151
00:06:03,230 --> 00:06:06,365
Weird one, too, and not just
'cause of the obvious

152
00:06:06,367 --> 00:06:08,300
buck naked, deep-fried
head thing.

153
00:06:08,302 --> 00:06:13,171
But someone also shaved
this poor guy's entire body.

154
00:06:13,173 --> 00:06:16,108
Hmm.
Well, maybe our poor killer's
just chaetophobic.

155
00:06:16,110 --> 00:06:17,509
Fear of hair.

156
00:06:17,511 --> 00:06:18,677
Always fun when
they turn up in Hell.

157
00:06:18,679 --> 00:06:21,279
Lots of wigs involved.

158
00:06:21,281 --> 00:06:25,117
But I'm pretty sure...

159
00:06:25,119 --> 00:06:26,885
(sniffs)

160
00:06:26,887 --> 00:06:28,754
...this guy got a bath
in bleach.

161
00:06:28,756 --> 00:06:30,455
CHLOE: So, whoever
dumped him is a pro.

162
00:06:30,457 --> 00:06:33,191
It's like he just vanished off
the face of the Earth.
ELLA: I know.

163
00:06:33,193 --> 00:06:36,695
But it's pretty tough for
someone to cover every track.

164
00:06:36,697 --> 00:06:39,498
If anyone can find something,
it's you, Ella.

165
00:06:39,500 --> 00:06:41,533
Aw, that is so sweet!

166
00:06:41,535 --> 00:06:42,934
LUCIFER: Yes, well,
u-until you do,

167
00:06:42,936 --> 00:06:45,203
I've got some personal business
I need to tend to.

168
00:06:45,205 --> 00:06:48,106
'Cause, you know, you're not
so much with the nice words,

169
00:06:48,108 --> 00:06:49,608
but when they come out...

170
00:06:52,112 --> 00:06:54,079
(knocks on door)

171
00:06:54,081 --> 00:06:55,514
(sighs)

172
00:06:56,350 --> 00:06:57,549
Doctor.
Hi.

173
00:06:57,551 --> 00:07:00,152
Lucifer, what's up?

174
00:07:00,154 --> 00:07:01,386
I'm wondering if
you've seen Amenadiel.

175
00:07:01,388 --> 00:07:02,654
Nope.

176
00:07:02,656 --> 00:07:06,425
Haven't seen<i> that </i>
family member. No.

177
00:07:06,427 --> 00:07:08,493
Can you stop being weird
and just let me in?

178
00:07:09,296 --> 00:07:10,729
Mum.

179
00:07:10,731 --> 00:07:13,064
What are you doing here?
Oh, you know,

180
00:07:13,066 --> 00:07:15,500
girl stuff.

181
00:07:15,502 --> 00:07:17,436
LUCIFER: (chuckles)
Naked girl stuff?

182
00:07:17,438 --> 00:07:20,172
Dr. Linda, I had no idea.

183
00:07:20,174 --> 00:07:21,873
(laughs)

184
00:07:21,875 --> 00:07:23,475
What is that?

185
00:07:27,648 --> 00:07:30,949
All right,
out with it, Mother.

186
00:07:30,951 --> 00:07:32,517
It's nothing.

187
00:07:32,519 --> 00:07:33,618
That spoiled brat,

188
00:07:33,620 --> 00:07:35,620
Chet Ruiz, stabbed me,

189
00:07:35,622 --> 00:07:36,922
and now I'm bleeding light.

190
00:07:36,924 --> 00:07:39,157
It's... it's no big deal.

191
00:07:39,159 --> 00:07:40,826
What?

192
00:07:40,828 --> 00:07:42,260
That's a huge deal.

193
00:07:42,262 --> 00:07:44,663
Mum, if your powers are
returning to this degree,

194
00:07:44,665 --> 00:07:47,632
then your human body won't be
able to contain it, you'll...

195
00:07:47,634 --> 00:07:48,934
you'll burst.

196
00:07:48,936 --> 00:07:50,469
Oh, no.

197
00:07:50,471 --> 00:07:51,903
I need to find Amenadiel now.

198
00:07:51,905 --> 00:07:53,238
I'd rather you didn't.

199
00:07:53,240 --> 00:07:54,673
I mean, it's bad enough

200
00:07:54,675 --> 00:07:55,907
that you'll be worried.
No, that's just it, Mum.

201
00:07:55,909 --> 00:07:58,977
Amenadiel has the missing
piece of the sword.

202
00:07:58,979 --> 00:08:00,912
You're k... you're kidding.

203
00:08:00,914 --> 00:08:03,548
Son, why didn't
you say something?

204
00:08:03,550 --> 00:08:07,219
Now we can finally ignite it and
cut through the Gates of Heaven

205
00:08:07,221 --> 00:08:12,057
and I can see my... I can...
I can see my children.

206
00:08:12,059 --> 00:08:16,561
Yes. Yes, but for now,
I need to find Amenadiel

207
00:08:16,563 --> 00:08:18,497
and you need
to stay away from humans.

208
00:08:18,499 --> 00:08:20,499
You're a... ticking bomb.

209
00:08:20,501 --> 00:08:21,900
Uh, um, actually,

210
00:08:21,902 --> 00:08:26,638
speaking of that, I...
may have already

211
00:08:26,640 --> 00:08:30,542
harmed... someone.

212
00:08:32,379 --> 00:08:33,512
Oh, no.

213
00:08:33,514 --> 00:08:34,813
No, no, no.

214
00:08:34,815 --> 00:08:36,848
I just came from a crime scene--
the man with a burned head.

215
00:08:36,850 --> 00:08:38,416
Please tell me that isn't Chet.

216
00:08:38,418 --> 00:08:40,952
The detective
is on that case.

217
00:08:40,954 --> 00:08:43,255
Well, not to worry.
I had a pro clean up the mess.

218
00:08:43,257 --> 00:08:45,240
You don't understand.

219
00:08:45,241 --> 00:08:47,224
The detective is good,
annoyingly good.

220
00:08:47,227 --> 00:08:49,861
Well, then we just need
to find Amenadiel, don't we?

221
00:08:49,863 --> 00:08:51,796
Yes.
And get the piece.

222
00:08:51,798 --> 00:08:53,398
Because if we don't
get you back to Heaven

223
00:08:53,400 --> 00:08:54,733
before the detective
gets to you,

224
00:08:54,735 --> 00:08:58,103
then she is quite
literally toast.

225
00:08:59,439 --> 00:09:00,872
(sighs)

226
00:09:00,874 --> 00:09:02,874
♪ ♪

227
00:09:15,188 --> 00:09:16,555
Did you slip
on a banana peel, too?

228
00:09:16,557 --> 00:09:19,024
What?
I'm afraid you're
gonna need surgery.

229
00:09:19,693 --> 00:09:21,159
Don't fight it.

230
00:09:21,161 --> 00:09:22,460
The kid's fierce.

231
00:09:22,462 --> 00:09:24,129
I...

232
00:09:24,131 --> 00:09:26,464
So, I left Mum
in the wine cellar at Lux,

233
00:09:26,466 --> 00:09:28,166
and that's the situation.

234
00:09:28,168 --> 00:09:29,401
(inhales sharply)
Ouch.

235
00:09:29,403 --> 00:09:30,969
Baby.

236
00:09:30,971 --> 00:09:32,971
I still don't get
why you're here.

237
00:09:32,973 --> 00:09:35,774
Because I need the best
bounty hunter out there.

238
00:09:35,776 --> 00:09:36,975
I can deal
with the detective,

239
00:09:36,977 --> 00:09:38,643
but I need you
to find Amenadiel.

240
00:09:38,645 --> 00:09:40,579
Then we can get the pendant,
assemble the sword

241
00:09:40,581 --> 00:09:42,581
before Mum spews
light everywhere.

242
00:09:42,583 --> 00:09:44,249
You don't have
to speak in code.

243
00:09:44,251 --> 00:09:45,450
I can handle adult stuff.

244
00:09:45,452 --> 00:09:46,818
MAZE: So what if
your mother explodes?

245
00:09:46,820 --> 00:09:49,721
Why should I care?

246
00:09:49,723 --> 00:09:52,424
Because many, many humans
could get hurt.

247
00:09:52,426 --> 00:09:53,858
Yeah, and?

248
00:09:53,860 --> 00:09:55,660
Oh, nice try, Maze,
but I happen to know

249
00:09:55,662 --> 00:09:57,162
there's a few
that you care about.

250
00:09:59,199 --> 00:10:01,032
Fine.

251
00:10:01,034 --> 00:10:02,467
But you pay me
my standard fee.

252
00:10:02,469 --> 00:10:03,635
No freebies.

253
00:10:03,637 --> 00:10:04,903
Absolutely.

254
00:10:04,905 --> 00:10:06,338
Oh.

255
00:10:06,340 --> 00:10:07,739
Love me a lolli.

256
00:10:07,741 --> 00:10:10,976
Sorry, wussies don't get any.

257
00:10:15,515 --> 00:10:17,749
♪ ♪

258
00:10:17,751 --> 00:10:21,219
♪ My night is day, yeah... ♪

259
00:10:21,221 --> 00:10:24,990
So, I ran the prints,

260
00:10:24,992 --> 00:10:28,627
and it came back as
your brother Chet.

