517
00:20:09,008 --> 00:20:11,209
I simply can't
let Mom loose on Dad.

518
00:20:11,211 --> 00:20:13,144
Now, it is finally
time that I go back

519
00:20:13,146 --> 00:20:16,180
to being the loyal soldier
that he entrusted me to be.

520
00:20:16,182 --> 00:20:18,616
Mom is not
going anywhere!

521
00:20:18,618 --> 00:20:21,285
Well, I am afraid that we do not
have a choice, Brother!

522
00:20:21,287 --> 00:20:22,653
Mum's powers
are returning,

523
00:20:22,655 --> 00:20:25,489
and it won't be long
before we can't contain them.

524
00:20:25,491 --> 00:20:27,225
I mean, she's already
killed one person,

525
00:20:27,227 --> 00:20:29,927
and now the detective is on a...

526
00:20:29,929 --> 00:20:32,129
the detective is on her case.

527
00:20:32,131 --> 00:20:33,464
So, please,
no discussion.

528
00:20:33,466 --> 00:20:36,334
Mum has to go!
(elevator bell dings)

529
00:20:36,336 --> 00:20:39,003
MAZE:
She already has.

530
00:20:40,506 --> 00:20:42,440
Your mother's gone.

531
00:20:43,710 --> 00:20:45,710
What?

532
00:20:45,712 --> 00:20:48,112
MOM: It's Cheval
something or other.

533
00:20:48,114 --> 00:20:50,948
It's valuable,
so it must be good.

534
00:20:54,387 --> 00:20:57,288
I wasn't expecting to see you

535
00:20:57,290 --> 00:20:58,623
or your...
(chuckles)

536
00:20:58,625 --> 00:21:00,925
deadly light back so soon.

537
00:21:00,927 --> 00:21:02,793
Well, something's
been bothering me.

538
00:21:02,795 --> 00:21:05,596
When you first
saw my wound...

539
00:21:05,598 --> 00:21:07,798
you asked if Lucifer
had done it.

540
00:21:08,668 --> 00:21:10,268
What did you
mean by that?

541
00:21:10,270 --> 00:21:11,969
I meant nothing by it.

542
00:21:11,971 --> 00:21:12,803
(chuckles):
You know?

543
00:21:12,805 --> 00:21:15,172
Meaningless brain fart,
you know?

544
00:21:15,174 --> 00:21:17,808
Just blah. Came out.

545
00:21:17,810 --> 00:21:20,011
There was a lot
going on that day.

546
00:21:20,013 --> 00:21:21,545
Hmm.

547
00:21:21,547 --> 00:21:24,548
I don't think so.

548
00:21:24,550 --> 00:21:27,018
I think, in fact,

549
00:21:27,020 --> 00:21:28,786
that you know something.

550
00:21:28,788 --> 00:21:30,554
I don't want to
hurt you, Linda.

551
00:21:30,556 --> 00:21:33,758
I... am running...

552
00:21:33,760 --> 00:21:35,559
out of time.

553
00:21:35,561 --> 00:21:38,396
You've seen what's
happening to me.

554
00:21:38,398 --> 00:21:42,166
So you can either
tell me what you know

555
00:21:42,168 --> 00:21:44,302
over a glass of wine

556
00:21:44,304 --> 00:21:48,906
or over your own
charbroiled corpse.

557
00:21:48,908 --> 00:21:50,574
Your choice.

558
00:21:54,814 --> 00:21:56,847
I came here to grill
Kathleen on the false alibi.

559
00:21:56,849 --> 00:21:59,684
DAN: Whoa. Somebody
already had, huh?

560
00:21:59,686 --> 00:22:01,552
Yeah.

561
00:22:01,554 --> 00:22:02,753
It's Ava Lyon.

562
00:22:02,755 --> 00:22:04,755
I'm thinking whoever killed Chet

563
00:22:04,757 --> 00:22:07,191
hired the Lyon sisters
to clean up,

564
00:22:07,193 --> 00:22:08,659
then cleaned up the cleaner.

565
00:22:09,495 --> 00:22:10,795
Excuse me, what is going on?

566
00:22:10,797 --> 00:22:11,796
I work here.

567
00:22:12,632 --> 00:22:14,765
Ava!

568
00:22:14,767 --> 00:22:16,067
Stop.

569
00:22:16,069 --> 00:22:18,836
(crying):
Oh, my God.

570
00:22:18,838 --> 00:22:20,771
What did I do?

571
00:22:20,773 --> 00:22:24,041
KATHLEEN:
<i> It's me, only me.</i>

572
00:22:24,043 --> 00:22:26,410
Ava knew nothing about it.

573
00:22:28,081 --> 00:22:29,880
I wasn't lying about Brad.

574
00:22:29,882 --> 00:22:31,615
I did get back
together with him,

575
00:22:31,617 --> 00:22:35,252
but he gambles a lot,
and he needed money.

576
00:22:35,254 --> 00:22:40,691
Then I got this call
offering me a hundred grand.

577
00:22:42,829 --> 00:22:45,363
Who hired you?

578
00:22:45,365 --> 00:22:47,531
Who killed Chet and your sister?

579
00:22:47,533 --> 00:22:51,102
Maybe Ava's death was a warning.

580
00:22:51,104 --> 00:22:53,371
For me to keep
my mouth shut.

581
00:22:53,373 --> 00:22:55,840
Maybe if I don't say anything...

582
00:22:55,842 --> 00:22:57,908
(sighs)

583
00:23:00,947 --> 00:23:03,280
So how do we find Mom?

584
00:23:03,282 --> 00:23:05,783
Follow the trail
of roasted humans?

585
00:23:05,785 --> 00:23:08,252
Well, if anyone can find
that wily goddess, it's Maze.

586
00:23:08,254 --> 00:23:10,454
She's on it.
(phone ringing)

587
00:23:12,658 --> 00:23:14,158
Detective.
Everything all right?

588
00:23:14,160 --> 00:23:15,426
CHLOE:
We found a body.

589
00:23:15,428 --> 00:23:16,427
Another body?

590
00:23:16,429 --> 00:23:17,428
A burned head.

591
00:23:17,430 --> 00:23:19,063
Same burned head?
CHLOE: Yes.

592
00:23:19,065 --> 00:23:21,799
So, what, you think whoever
killed Chet killed again?

593
00:23:21,801 --> 00:23:23,701
Look, Lucifer,
it's a long story,

594
00:23:23,703 --> 00:23:25,703
but the second victim
is Ava Lyon.

595
00:23:25,705 --> 00:23:27,538
She's one of
the cleaners we met.

596
00:23:27,540 --> 00:23:29,039
I have her sister Kathleen here,

597
00:23:29,041 --> 00:23:31,208
but she's not saying anything--
she's scared.

598
00:23:31,210 --> 00:23:32,777
So I need you to come here,

599
00:23:32,779 --> 00:23:34,812
and I need you to do
your mojo thing.

600
00:23:34,814 --> 00:23:37,882
Yes, Detective,
believe me when I say

601
00:23:37,884 --> 00:23:40,451
I want to find the killer
as much as you do.

602
00:23:40,453 --> 00:23:41,886
Hello, boys.

603
00:23:41,888 --> 00:23:42,820
Mum.

604
00:23:42,822 --> 00:23:44,422
What? What? What's going on?

605
00:23:44,424 --> 00:23:46,690
I-I'm so sorry. My mum's here.

606
00:23:46,692 --> 00:23:48,426
I-I've got to rush.

607
00:23:48,428 --> 00:23:50,795
Good luck with
Kathleen. Ciao.

608
00:23:50,797 --> 00:23:52,163
Damn it.

609
00:23:52,165 --> 00:23:53,764
What's wrong?
Lucifer.

610
00:23:53,766 --> 00:23:54,899
He's...

611
00:23:54,901 --> 00:23:57,368
He's hiding something from me,
I can tell.

612
00:23:57,370 --> 00:23:59,703
Oh, you know what? It's probably
just embarrassing family stuff.

613
00:23:59,705 --> 00:24:01,772
I mean, they seem
totally bonkers.

614
00:24:01,774 --> 00:24:02,940
Yeah.

615
00:24:02,942 --> 00:24:04,308
Maybe.

616
00:24:04,310 --> 00:24:08,179
He is with
his step-mom now, so...

617
00:24:08,181 --> 00:24:10,581
So maybe...

618
00:24:10,583 --> 00:24:13,284
maybe he's not hiding
<i> something</i> from me,

619
00:24:13,286 --> 00:24:14,552
but<i> someone.</i>

620
00:24:14,554 --> 00:24:17,688
Someone who knew Chet.

621
00:24:17,690 --> 00:24:20,624
And someone I still don't trust.

622
00:24:20,626 --> 00:24:21,992
AMENADIEL:
What have you been doing?

623
00:24:21,994 --> 00:24:24,228
Oh... this and that.

624
00:24:24,230 --> 00:24:26,964
<i> This</i> being firing up
the celestial barbecue

625
00:24:26,966 --> 00:24:29,567
so<i> that</i> you can
grill another head?

626
00:24:29,569 --> 00:24:31,969
No. I just needed
to get cleaned up.

627
00:24:31,971 --> 00:24:33,604
Get some air.

628
00:24:33,606 --> 00:24:35,606
I was feeling
a little claustrophobic.

629
00:24:35,608 --> 00:24:39,543
Don't you just hate
being kept in the dark?

630
00:24:41,881 --> 00:24:44,615
The good news is
you found Amenadiel.

631
00:24:44,617 --> 00:24:47,852
So we have the piece?

632
00:24:47,854 --> 00:24:48,752
Yes.

633
00:24:48,754 --> 00:24:50,721
Yes. Well, interesting
story, actually.

634
00:24:50,723 --> 00:24:52,056
Why don't you
tell her, Brother?

635
00:24:52,058 --> 00:24:54,225
Oh, no, no, no, no, no.
This one's all you.

636
00:24:54,227 --> 00:24:56,093
Brother, I insist.

637
00:24:57,497 --> 00:24:59,263
Thank you.
(chuckles softly)

638
00:24:59,265 --> 00:25:00,664
Right. Well, uh,

639
00:25:00,666 --> 00:25:02,032
upon careful
consideration,

640
00:25:02,034 --> 00:25:04,168
we've decided this whole
Flaming Sword plan

641
00:25:04,170 --> 00:25:05,369
is a crap idea.

642
00:25:05,371 --> 00:25:06,504
Yes, crap.

643
00:25:06,506 --> 00:25:07,638
Mm. Have you ever considered

644
00:25:07,640 --> 00:25:09,740
finding, well,
I don't know,

645
00:25:09,742 --> 00:25:11,008
a-a place of your own?

646
00:25:11,010 --> 00:25:13,711
Yeah. Somewhere away
from Dad, maybe?

647
00:25:13,713 --> 00:25:14,512
Yes.

648
00:25:14,514 --> 00:25:16,247
LUCIFER:
Somewhere familiar,

649
00:25:16,249 --> 00:25:18,249
warmer, perhaps?

650
00:25:20,052 --> 00:25:23,521
You want...
you want me back in Hell?

651
00:25:23,523 --> 00:25:25,256
Well, not<i> in</i> Hell,
per se,

652
00:25:25,258 --> 00:25:26,524
but in charge of Hell.

653
00:25:26,526 --> 00:25:28,392
I mean, after all,
it is a kingdom

654
00:25:28,394 --> 00:25:29,693
without a ruler.

655
00:25:29,695 --> 00:25:30,961
He is right.

656
00:25:30,963 --> 00:25:33,397
I mean, there's a great
opportunity for upward mobility.

657
00:25:33,399 --> 00:25:35,099
Lick of paint
here or there.

658
00:25:35,101 --> 00:25:37,668
The columns
would look great in white.

659
00:25:39,372 --> 00:25:41,572
Beige?

660
00:25:43,543 --> 00:25:45,509
(chuckles softly)

661
00:25:45,511 --> 00:25:47,311
So it's true.

662
00:25:47,313 --> 00:25:49,947
You<i> are</i> working
against me.

663
00:25:49,949 --> 00:25:55,252
You never planned
on going with me to Heaven.

664
00:25:55,254 --> 00:25:56,387
Wait.

665
00:25:56,389 --> 00:25:58,389
How did you find out?

666
00:25:58,391 --> 00:26:01,759
Well, I persuaded...

667
00:26:01,761 --> 00:26:03,694
your little doctor.

668
00:26:03,696 --> 00:26:06,030
I'm sorry.
I had no choice.

669
00:26:06,032 --> 00:26:07,298
What did you do?

670
00:26:08,534 --> 00:26:10,167
Mum.

671
00:26:10,169 --> 00:26:11,335
AMENADIEL:
Mom.

672
00:26:11,337 --> 00:26:12,736
Listen, I understand.

673
00:26:12,738 --> 00:26:14,138
You're angry.

674
00:26:14,140 --> 00:26:17,641
Oh, I'm not angry.

675
00:26:18,544 --> 00:26:21,312
Just disappointed.

676
00:26:21,314 --> 00:26:22,646
(Lucifer and Amenadiel grunt)

677
00:26:28,154 --> 00:26:29,620
(groaning)

678
00:26:31,591 --> 00:26:33,924
Give me the piece!

679
00:26:33,926 --> 00:26:35,259
No, Mom.

680
00:26:36,996 --> 00:26:39,063
You're gonna have to kill me.

681
00:26:43,169 --> 00:26:47,304
Guess I'll have to find
another way, won't I?

682
00:26:54,180 --> 00:26:55,613
Well, now look
what you've made her do.

683
00:26:55,615 --> 00:26:56,747
I've just had this tuned!

684
00:26:56,749 --> 00:27:00,718
Me? How about you
suggesting Hell

685
00:27:00,720 --> 00:27:03,220
as a retirement home? Nice.

686
00:27:03,222 --> 00:27:04,321
Maybe if you had just

687
00:27:04,323 --> 00:27:05,456
mentioned the pottery class

688
00:27:05,458 --> 00:27:08,525
or water aerobics,
she would have gone for it.

689
00:27:08,527 --> 00:27:09,994
Oh, and did you have
a better idea?

690
00:27:09,996 --> 00:27:13,097
Mom's coming undone, Luci.

691
00:27:14,734 --> 00:27:16,266
In every way.
I know.

692
00:27:16,268 --> 00:27:18,636
And she doesn't care
who she hurts anymore.

693
00:27:18,638 --> 00:27:20,037
Linda.

694
00:27:20,039 --> 00:27:21,338
I'll go check on Linda.

695
00:27:21,340 --> 00:27:23,273
You go after Mom;
she'll listen to you.

696
00:27:23,275 --> 00:27:25,309
But, Luci, don't you dare
promise her that piece,

697
00:27:25,311 --> 00:27:27,177
because I won't
give it to her.

698
00:27:32,418 --> 00:27:35,719
♪ ♪

699
00:27:42,061 --> 00:27:43,894
Well, well.
Someone's clever.

700
00:27:43,896 --> 00:27:46,330
How did you get me?

701
00:27:46,332 --> 00:27:48,465
Wasn't that hard.
We tracked your phone.

702
00:27:48,467 --> 00:27:52,369
No, I mean, how did you
figure out I was the bad guy?

703
00:27:52,371 --> 00:27:55,072
Did Little Miss Dandy Lyon
tell you?

704
00:27:55,074 --> 00:27:56,940
It's over, Charlotte.
Put your hands up.

705
00:27:56,942 --> 00:27:58,709
Oh, don't worry, I'm
not going to resist.

706
00:27:58,711 --> 00:28:00,844
I'll tell you everything
you want to know.

707
00:28:00,846 --> 00:28:03,347
I just have one small request.

708
00:28:06,152 --> 00:28:08,285
(phone ringing)

709
00:28:08,287 --> 00:28:09,820
Detective.

710
00:28:09,822 --> 00:28:11,221
Any chance you've seen my Mu...

711
00:28:11,223 --> 00:28:12,823
MOM:
Looking for little ol' me?

712
00:28:12,825 --> 00:28:13,891
You were right, dear.

713
00:28:13,893 --> 00:28:16,694
Your detective
is quite good.

714
00:28:16,696 --> 00:28:18,095
(Mom chuckles)

715
00:28:18,097 --> 00:28:19,463
(whispers):
She caught me.

716
00:28:19,465 --> 00:28:20,564
Where are you?

717
00:28:20,566 --> 00:28:21,699
Santa Monica Pier.

718
00:28:21,701 --> 00:28:22,866
Such a beautiful place.

719
00:28:22,868 --> 00:28:25,335
So many people.

720
00:28:25,337 --> 00:28:27,204
If you hurt anyone, Mum,

721
00:28:27,206 --> 00:28:28,539
if you hurt her...

722
00:28:28,541 --> 00:28:31,408
And if you and your brother had
just given me what I needed.

723
00:28:31,410 --> 00:28:32,710
But who knows?

724
00:28:32,712 --> 00:28:34,111
Maybe you still can.

725
00:28:34,980 --> 00:28:36,413
Okay, that's enough.

726
00:28:36,415 --> 00:28:38,282
Mum!

727
00:28:39,318 --> 00:28:40,317
Start talking.

728
00:28:40,319 --> 00:28:42,820
Just the two of us.

729
00:28:42,822 --> 00:28:44,221
If that's all right.

730
00:28:44,223 --> 00:28:47,291
I'd rather not
put Daniel in...

731
00:28:47,293 --> 00:28:49,593
an awkward position.

732
00:28:49,595 --> 00:28:52,730
Hate to ruin all the good ones
we've been in.

733
00:28:52,732 --> 00:28:54,331
(clears throat)

734
00:28:54,333 --> 00:28:55,599
Can we go outside?

735
00:28:55,601 --> 00:28:56,867
Mm-hmm.

736
00:28:56,869 --> 00:28:59,069
I'll be fine.

737
00:29:08,547 --> 00:29:10,781
I'll miss you, Daniel.

738
00:29:10,783 --> 00:29:13,383
You are my
favorite human.

739
00:29:18,624 --> 00:29:20,324
(phone ringing)

740
00:29:20,326 --> 00:29:21,525
Hey. You find Mom?

741
00:29:21,527 --> 00:29:24,461
She's on Santa Monica Pier,
and she wants the piece.

742
00:29:24,463 --> 00:29:26,330
(horn honks, tires screech)

743
00:29:26,332 --> 00:29:28,665
We have to give it to her,
Amenadiel.

744
00:29:28,667 --> 00:29:30,234
We've run out of options.

745
00:29:30,236 --> 00:29:31,235
Please.

746
00:29:31,237 --> 00:29:33,370
Brother, please.

747
00:29:33,372 --> 00:29:36,940
She... she has Chloe.

748
00:29:40,913 --> 00:29:43,013
Linda! You here?!

749
00:29:43,015 --> 00:29:44,948
I'm tracking Lucifer's mom,

750
00:29:44,950 --> 00:29:47,985
and I think she might
be on her way.

751
00:29:50,656 --> 00:29:53,090
(groans weakly)

752
00:29:53,092 --> 00:29:54,525
Oh, no.

753
00:29:54,527 --> 00:29:57,127
No, no, no!

754
00:30:00,766 --> 00:30:02,699
Linda.

755
00:30:02,701 --> 00:30:04,568
Hey. It's okay.

756
00:30:04,570 --> 00:30:06,637
I'm here. Okay?

757
00:30:06,639 --> 00:30:08,105
You're gonna be fine.

758
00:30:10,776 --> 00:30:13,210
She did this to you, didn't she?

759
00:30:13,212 --> 00:30:16,947
(crying): She wanted to know
what Lucifer's plans were.

760
00:30:16,949 --> 00:30:18,949
I didn't want
to tell her.

761
00:30:18,951 --> 00:30:21,051
I tried to resist.
I'm so sorry.

762
00:30:21,053 --> 00:30:23,086
It's not your fault, okay?

763
00:30:23,088 --> 00:30:25,422
And you're going to be fine.

764
00:30:25,424 --> 00:30:26,757
I promise.

765
00:30:26,759 --> 00:30:28,425
I'm-I'm gonna fix you.

766
00:30:28,427 --> 00:30:29,993
Okay?

767
00:30:35,568 --> 00:30:37,034
(crying):
Help me.

768
00:30:38,971 --> 00:30:41,338
Hello, Daniel.

769
00:30:41,340 --> 00:30:42,339
Whoa!

770
00:30:42,341 --> 00:30:43,874
Whoa, whoa!

771
00:30:43,876 --> 00:30:45,342
She kissed me.

772
00:30:45,344 --> 00:30:46,577
Literally no idea
what you're talking about.

773
00:30:46,579 --> 00:30:47,578
Just get your hands up.

774
00:30:47,580 --> 00:30:48,679
No, don't be silly.

775
00:30:48,681 --> 00:30:50,113
I'm not gonna stab you.

776
00:30:50,115 --> 00:30:51,481
I'm just looking
for something.

777
00:30:51,483 --> 00:30:53,417
Come on, up. Up!

778
00:30:56,255 --> 00:30:58,322
What are you looking for?

779
00:30:58,324 --> 00:30:59,489
Uh...

780
00:30:59,491 --> 00:31:01,024
Hello.
Whoa.

781
00:31:01,026 --> 00:31:02,926
What the...?

782
00:31:03,462 --> 00:31:04,862
Whoa, whoa, whoa.

783
00:31:04,864 --> 00:31:06,263
Ah.

